{{vgname2|Samsung Galaxy|ko=삼성 갤럭시|简称'''SSG'''}}是韩国公司[[三星电子|三星电子]]旗下的职业[[电子竞技|电子竞技]][[企业队|企业队伍]]。成立期间，队伍下设《[[英雄联盟|英雄联盟]]》、《[[星际争霸系列|星际争霸]]》以及《[[星际争霸II|星际争霸II]]》分部。

Samsung Galaxy《英雄联盟》分部成立于2013年9月7日，他们收购了[[MVP_(电子竞技)|MVP]]的两支队伍MVP Blue和MVP White并更名为“Samsung Galaxy Blue”（'''SSB'''，俗称'''三星蓝'''）和“Samsung Galaxy White”（'''SSW'''，俗称'''三星白'''）<ref>{{Cite news |title=삼성전자, 갤럭시 프로게임단으로 새출발 |url=http://sports.news.naver.com/sports/index.nhn?category=e_sports&ctg=news&mod=read&office_id=439&article_id=0000000310 |publisher=This Is Game |date=2013-09-07 |accessdate=2020-07-03 |archive-date=2016-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215055015/http://sports.news.naver.com/sports/index.nhn?category=e_sports |dead-url=no }}</ref>。Samsung White获得了[[英雄联盟2014赛季全球总决赛|英雄联盟2014赛季全球总决赛]]冠军<ref>{{cite news |title=Side by side comparison of 2014 World Champions Samsung White versus 2015 SK Telecom T1 |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/side-by-side-comparison-of-2014-world-champions-samsung-white-versus-2015-sk-tel-6900 |accessdate=2019-08-04 |work=Dot Esports |date=2015-10-22 |archive-date=2019-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804055440/https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/side-by-side-comparison-of-2014-world-champions-samsung-white-versus-2015-sk-tel-6900 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=One of these things is not like the others: Samsung's unlikely Worlds appearance |url=https://www.thescoreesports.com/lol/news/10247-one-of-these-things-is-not-like-the-others-samsung-s-unlikely-worlds-appearance |accessdate=2019-08-04 |work=theScore esports |date=2016-09-19 |language=en |archive-date=2019-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804055440/https://www.thescoreesports.com/lol/news/10247-one-of-these-things-is-not-like-the-others-samsung-s-unlikely-worlds-appearance |dead-url=no }}</ref>。两支队伍随后进行了合并并以“Samsung Galaxy”之名参赛，新队伍并获得了[[英雄联盟2016赛季全球总决赛|英雄联盟2016赛季全球总决赛]]亚军和[[英雄联盟2017赛季全球总决赛|英雄联盟2017赛季全球总决赛]]冠军<ref name="2016 LoL Championship finals">{{cite web|last1=Lam|first1=Kien|title=SK Telecom T1 wins World Championship again|url=http://eu.lolesports.com/en/articles/sk-telecom-t1-wins-world-championship-again|website=LoL eSports|publisher=Riot Games|accessdate=2016-10-30|archive-date=2016-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031024809/http://eu.lolesports.com/en/articles/sk-telecom-t1-wins-world-championship-again|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

